amdgpu: uvd_v4_2 — copy fw to GTT BO and bind at GART 0x300000000 (v76d-β-2-A2)

v76d-β-2-A1.5 confirmed the fault is GONE when we bind both 0x300000000
and VA 0 to a zero-filled dummy page, but the VCPU still silently stalls
(STATUS=0x4, never reaches bit 1). The interpretation: the firmware is
reading zeros at 0x300000000 — its hardcoded address for region 1
(firmware target) — and zero bytes aren't valid microcode/data, so it
can't execute meaningful work.

This patch makes the firmware read REAL contents at 0x300000000.

Implementation:
- New helper uvd_v4_2_setup_fw_mirror_liverpool() in uvd_v4_2.c
- Allocates a 1920 KB GTT BO (matching Sony's region 1 size of 0x1E0000)
- memcpy the actual UVD firmware bytes (from adev->uvd.fw->data) into the
  start of the BO; leaves the rest zero (save/restore area)
- Calls amdgpu_gart_bind to point GART entries at 0x300000000 to this
  BO's physical pages — overwrites the dummy binding installed by
  v76d-β-2-A in gmc_v7_0_gart_enable
- amdgpu_gart_invalidate_tlb so the new PTEs take effect

Called once-only via static guard `uvd_fw_mirror_done`. The BO is
intentionally never freed — it's a permanent per-device mirror for the
duration of the kernel's life.

Hooked into uvd_v4_2_start_liverpool early (before the VCPU start
sequence), so the bind is in place by the time the firmware begins
executing.

Sony's UVD region layout (Ghidra-derived):
  Region 1 (firmware,  1920 KB) → vmid 4 / 0x300000000..0x3001E0000
  Region 2 (heap/IB,   1168 KB) → vmid 4 / 0x3001E0000..0x300304000
  Region 3 (msgq,        16 KB) → vmid 4 / 0x300304000..0x300308000

For this patch we ONLY bind region 1 (the firmware). If the firmware
also requires regions 2/3 to be reachable from 0x3001E0000+, we'll see
a new fault at one of those addresses on the next iteration.

Expected hardware signals:

  ✅ VCPU sets STATUS bit 1 within 2 seconds — firmware boots
     successfully and the ring test proceeds. UVD works!

  🟡 Fault appears at 0x3001E0000 or 0x300304000 — firmware progressed
     past region 1 and needs region 2 or 3 mapped. Cheap fix: extend
     this patch to also alloc and bind regions 2/3.

  🟡 Different fault elsewhere — firmware did execute, but its state
     machine hit some other config dependency we haven't mapped.

  ❌ Same silent stall — the firmware needs something fundamentally
     different at 0x300000000 (not just its own bytes). May need to
     prepend a header or use a different offset within region 1.

Diagnostic prints on success:
  "ps4 uvd: bound fw mirror at GART virtual 0x300000000
   (BO gpu_addr=0x..., fw_size=N, region1_size=1966080)"

Memory cost: ~1920 KB GTT per boot, never freed.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

